north_arrow.description: North arrow in upper-left corner of sewer site plan, labeled NORTH with compass rose. Arrow points upper-left, tilted left of vertical.

front_identification.description: ADU entry door is on the bottom wall of the floor plan (FRONT elevation with covered porch and 4x4 posts). On the site plan, the floor plan is rotated 90° clockwise — the front/entry wall faces LEFT toward the existing 4-bedroom house. The sub panel is noted at the 'back of ADU' with conduit from the left (house side), confirming back=right on site plan and front=left. The front faces slightly south of due left on the site plan.

elevation_analysis.entry_evidence: FRONT elevation shows long wall (36'-4") with covered porch, 4x4 posts, entry door (#1, 3'-0" swing door). Floor plan confirms ENTRY room with door #1 on this side.

site_plan_measurement.building_footprint_description: ADU rectangle in upper-right of lot, long axis runs roughly top-to-bottom (vertically) on the page. Main house is to the left. Wyoming Street is on the far left.
site_plan_measurement.entry_wall_identification: The long wall on the LEFT side of the ADU footprint, facing toward the existing 4 Bedroom House. This is the FRONT wall (entry side).

entry_wall_edge.wall_runs_from: top to bottom, nearly vertical on the page but tilted approximately 6 degrees (top leans slightly right)
entry_wall_edge.entry_faces_outward: perpendicular outward from the wall, toward LEFT and slightly DOWN (toward main house), drawing angle ~264°

site_plan_measurement.cross_check: Entry direction points toward existing 4 Bedroom House — confirmed. Sewer lateral path runs from house to ADU in this direction.
